{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title=The Law Terms Act 1830 |parliament=Parliament of the United Kingdom |long_title=An Act for the more effectual Administration of Justice in England and Wales. |year=1830 |statute_book_chapter=11 Geo 4 & 1 Will 4 c 70 |introduced_by= |territorial_extent= |royal_assent=23 July 1830 |commencement=12 October 1830<ref>The Law Terms Act 1830, section 39</ref> |repeal_date= |amendments= |related_legislation= |repealing_legislation= |status= |original_text=https://books.google.com/books?id=eK5qQAEWLiYC&dq=Statutes%20at%20Large%2011%20Geo.IV%20%26%201%20Will.IV%201830&pg=PA445#v=onepage&q&f=false |legislation_history= |revised_text= |}}
'''The Law Terms Act 1830''' (11 Geo 4 & 1 Will 4 c 70) was an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] that made various changes to the court system of [[England and Wales]].
Section 8 granted direct [[appeal (law)|appeal]] from the [[Court of Common Pleas (England)|Court of Common Pleas]] to the [[Court of Exchequer Chamber]], rather than indirectly through the [[King's Bench]].<ref>Cornish & Clark (1989) ''p.''25</ref>
Section 14 abolished the independent [[jurisdiction]] of the courts of session of the [[County Palatine of Chester]].<ref>[http://www.statutelaw.gov.uk/content.aspx?activetextdocid=1516541 Reference in the Distress for Rent Act 1737] at the [[UK Statute Law Database]]</ref><ref>Yates (1856) ''p.''7</ref>
Section 15 was repealed by section 56 of, and Part IV of Schedule 11 to, the [[Courts Act 1971]].
In a report dated 27 September 1985, the [[Law Commission (England and Wales)|Law Commission]] and the [[Scottish Law Commission]] said that section 32 was the only provision that had not been repealed. They said that local consultation had confirmed it was obsolete and unnecessary. They recommended the whole Act be repealed.<ref>The Law Commission and the Scottish Law Commission. Statute Law Revision: Twelfth Report. Law Com 150. SLC 99. Cmnd 9648. Pages 6 and 34.</ref> The Act was repealed by Group 1 of [http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1986/12/schedule/1/part/I/enacted Part I] of Schedule 1 to the [[Statute Law (Repeals) Act 1986]].
